===Etymology 2===
Named by Dutch explorers Pieter Dirkszoon Keyser and Frederick de Houtman between 1595 and 1597. From {{L.}} ''[[Indus]]'', "[[Indian]]".
====Proper noun====
{{wikipedia|Indus (constellation)}}
'''Indus'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] sky between [[Grus]] and [[Pavo]]. It commemorates [[American]] [[Indian]]s.

